title: ● Frankens said that his rule was more important than that of his founders?
subtitle: Senator Al Franken confirmed that his vote in Parliament would be separate from the results of the Minnesota groupings but did not specifically indicate that his decision was "more important" than his constituents wanted.
author: Kim LaCapria
vclaim: Senator Al Franken told a CNN interviewer that his sentence as Superdigget was more important than that of the constituency.
